Feature: 1.1 Sign in to the App
    
  Given application URL is opened
Scenario: Standard user signs in successfully
    Given user enters "standard_user" into "Username" input
    And user enters "secret_sauce" into "Password" input
    When user clicks the "Login" button
    Then they should be successfully logged in
    And "Products" page should be visible
    
       
Scenario: Locked out user sees error message
          When the user enters the following credentials:
          | Username        | Password     |
          | locked_out_user | secret_sauce |
          And clicks the Login button
          Then they should see the error message "Sorry, this user has been locked out"
        
Scenario: Invalid credentials (invalid username)
        When the user enters invalid credentials:
         | Username          | Password |
         | standard          | secret_sauce |
        And clicks the Login button
        Then user should see an error message "Username and password do not match any user in this service"
        
Scenario: User leaves username field empty
    When the user leaves the "Username" field empty
    And user enters "secret_sauce" into "Password" input
    And clicks the "Login" button
    Then user should see an error message "Username is required"
    
Scenario: User leaves password field empty
    When the user leaves the "Password" field empty
    And user enters "standard_user" into "Username" input
    And clicks the "Login" button
    Then user should see an error message "Password is required"
    
    
Scenario: Check case sensitivity: User enters valid username with mixed case and correct password
    Given user enters "Standard_user" into "Username" input
    And user enters "secret_sauce" into "Password" input
    When user clicks the "Login" button
    Then user should see an error message "Username and password do not match any user in this service"
    
